    "The scale and precision of serial sectioning varies greatly between applications, ranging from sparse blocks, slices or thin sections that provide cross sectional overviews of specimen structure (e.g., Ørvig (1980)), to high resolution tomographic images which can be fully interrogated with volume image analysis techniques.",
